cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimizing energy efficiency in small cell networks. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the problem is formulated as a dynamic stochastic game between small cell base stations. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with optimizing bits per unit energy. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a joint power control and user scheduling approach. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also relevant as the paper deals with a game-theoretic approach to optimize energy efficiency in small cell networks.
